	<text>
		<body>
			<div>
				<pb facs="#facs_1" n="1"/>
				<p facs="#facs_1_r">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_67">(↑) you has been lost. But you should reckon with the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_60">(↑) I shall send you one set by [mail?], in case the one they sent</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_53">(↑) when I got your bill. - I got the proofs from Baylis just now. </l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_46">(↑) I forgot to write you that I have paid the <orgName ref="gnd-812629-X">O. U. P.</orgName> immediatly</l>
					</lg>
				</p>
				<p facs="#facs_1_r_35">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_74">(←) fact that all outward mail from  Gt. Britain takes much </l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_81">(←) longer than from America to England. </l>
					</lg>
				</p>
				<p facs="#facs_1_tr_1">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_8">
                            <orgName ref="gnd-5086316-2">Somerville College</orgName>,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_9">
                            <date when="1949-03-03">3 March 1949</date>.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_10">My dear <persName ref="gnd-118777378">Raymond</persName>,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_11">I came back yesterday and found your parcel!</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_12">It really is a mammoth one and its contents induced a kind</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_13">of orgie of eating, so that I immediately consumed several</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_14">items, cold and hungry as I was. Thanks a lot.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_15">I am afraid my last letter about the printing</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_16">has filled you with dismay. I had a long conversations</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_17">with <persName ref="gnd-116183853">Bing</persName> during the last days, interspersed with telephone</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_18">conversations with Baylis. The situation is this : obvious-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_19">ly it would be much better if the <orgName ref="gnd-1231301309">Trinity Press</orgName> could do</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_20">the job - from the point of view of relative speed, of the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_21">uniformity of the series, of the pleasantness of dealings,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_22">and of the price. Baylis' main objection is that they fear</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_23">they would not be able to do it to satisfactkon as, their</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_24">readers are not competent to cope with so much Greek. It</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_25">has now been suggested to them that the supervising of the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_26">Greek text could be done by us, and they are thinking it over.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_27">It is also possible that they might take it on, if we gave</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_28">up the idea of printing the Greek text at the beginning of</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_29">the <persName ref="gnd-118641778">Proclus </persName>passage and in the terthreia passage. They</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_30">would be able to do the Greek in the apparatus, and they</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_31">could send out the Apparatus Fontium as a whole, to be done</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_32">elsewhere. It seems to me that this suggestion is well worth</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_34">considering. Obviously, we would have to make a few additions</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_35">in me Greek apparatus, to indicate where Cousin is [quite] wrong [in his reading]</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_36">(3 or 4 cases), but it does not seem to me to be de rigeur</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_37">to print these passages in Greek. We could do that in the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_38">article on the Greek <persName ref="gnd-118641778">Proclus</persName> MSS. Please think it over and</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_39">send me a cable saying 'agreed', if you think the Greek could</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_40">be jettisoned, or 'not agreed', as the case may be. I want</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_41">you to understand that Baylis has not yet made it a condition</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_42">to give up these passages, he may stil decline the job all-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_43">together, or may think of a way of doing it in the original</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_44">form. But it may be the decisive factor. — If Baylis cannot</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_45">do it, Miss <persName ref="gnd-116183853">Bing</persName> does not want to go further afield but is</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_46">going to ask the <orgName ref="gnd-812629-X">O. U. P.</orgName> to do the estimate and the specimen</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_47">pages simultaneously. Her objections are that the <orgName ref="gnd-812629-X">O. U. P</orgName>
                        </l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_48">are slow, high-handed, and very expensive. But the <orgName ref="gnd-1008744-8">Cambridge</orgName>
                        </l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_49">Press are no better, and the Belgian Press is for various</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l">reasons out of the question. - What I wrote to you about</l>
					</lg>
				</p>
				<pb facs="#facs_2" n="2"/>
				<p facs="#facs_2_tr_2">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_1">muddle with the <ref target="https://explore.gnd.network/gnd/4006824-9">Phaedo </ref>apparatus appears to be one of</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_l">
                            <persName ref="gnd-122779983">Minio</persName>'s exaggerations. They did divide the apparatus</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_l_30">up according to typed pages, as the <orgName ref="gnd-812629-X">O. U. P.</orgName> seems to do</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_6">it immediately according to galley pages, he assumed that</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_7">the <orgName ref="gnd-1231301309">Trinity Press</orgName> would go on [like this] to the end and print the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_8">apparatus according to his typed pages, even when the text</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_l_37">was printed! But they told me that Baylis</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_11">has so far always been able to deal with apparatus quite</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_12">satisfactorily, even thouch he had a different way of</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_13">setting it in the first proofs from the one customary</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_14">with the University Presses. <persName ref="gnd-122779983">Mimio </persName>has calmed down and</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_15">praises the accuracy of their printing highly. </l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_16">I have for the moment postponed my journey to the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_17">end of March. But I am not going later than about the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_18">
                            <date when="1949-03-28">28th</date>. Otherwise there would not be any point in my going</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_19">at all, and I want to go. I think we should have collations,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_20">apart from the <persName ref="gnd-118594893">Plato </persName>lemmata, also of the first two or three</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_21">columns of <persName ref="gnd-118641778">Proclus</persName>' Prologue. If we are not going to print</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_22">the Greek text in the edition, but in the article, we might</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_l_65">find that [it?] is somewhat unsymmetrical [to] print [the end] by it-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_25">self. Also, there might be codices which one cannot satis-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_26">factorily classify by the end only, as there may be a diffe-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_27">rent source for the first half. The MS c seems to me a case</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_28">in point. Do you thint we should do that, or do you think</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_29">the 'Nikomachos-Kallimachos' test is sufficient ? - Please</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_30">believe that we are all doing our best to bring the <persName ref="gnd-118641778">Proclus</persName>
                        </l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_32">out and do not send impatient letters. But let me know</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_33">- in case I have to tell the <orgName ref="gnd-812629-X">O. U. P.</orgName> - how [many pages] you think</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_34">the <persName ref="gnd-129070807">Cusanus </persName>marginal notes will take up.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_35">What you write about the Middle west possibili-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_36">ties is very interesting indeed. My opinion is that if the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_37">following conditions are fulfilled : Good pay, real time for</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_38">work, adequate help (secretary, library facilities etc.)</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_39">it is almost your duty to accept - if the place is at all</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_40">bearable. Three or four years of quiet work, without the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_41">constant pressure of things to be done, would set you up</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_l_7">enormously, and it woul make an immense difference to your</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_l_14">career later on. The kindness of people at <orgName ref="gnd-2187-8">M.</orgName> is all very</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_46">well, but what about the people to whom you have earlier</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_47">obligations ? And it seems that at <orgName ref="gnd-2187-8">McGill </orgName>you will never</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_48">have time to spare. - Of course, you would have to be very</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_49">firm with yourself and not immediately divert your energies</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_50">to starting new schemes at the new place, but really settle</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_51">down to disentangling your old papers. The main thing is</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_52">to be sure that you would be left to do your work and that</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_53">you would have the possibility to visit European libraries</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_54">in the summer.</l>
					</lg>
				</p>
				<p facs="#facs_2_r">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_2_l_21">Yours</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_l_28">
                            <persName ref="gnd-1029912939">Lotti</persName>
                        </l>
					</lg>
				</p>
			</div>
